# Styling Guidelines

## Tailwind CSS Usage
- Use Tailwind utility classes for all styling
- Follow the design system defined in [tailwind.config.js](mdc:tailwind.config.js)
- Use CSS variables for theming (dark/light mode support)

## Color Scheme
- Primary colors: Use `hsl(var(--primary))` and variants
- Background: `hsl(var(--background))`
- Foreground: `hsl(var(--foreground))`
- Muted colors for secondary text: `text-muted-foreground`
- Card backgrounds: `hsl(var(--card))`

## Component Styling Patterns
- Container: `container mx-auto p-6 space-y-6`
- Grid layouts: `grid gap-4 md:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-4`
- Flex layouts: `flex items-center justify-between`
- Responsive design: Use `md:`, `lg:` prefixes

## Dark Mode
- Dark mode is supported via `class` strategy
- Use CSS variables for all colors to support theme switching
- Theme toggle available in [src/components/ThemeToggle.tsx](mdc:src/components/ThemeToggle.tsx)

## shadcn/ui Integration
- All UI components use the design tokens from [components.json](mdc:components.json)
- Style: "new-york" variant
- Base color: "neutral"
- CSS variables enabled for theming